      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KALKADOON DREAMING (9) made a winning start for the new stable when successful at Junee last week, getting home by a head after leading. Draws out a little on the second line so may need luck at some point but if it comes his way he can go on with the job. WARIEDA BOY (6) has had four runs this campaign and while yet to place he has clocked in fourth in the last two outings, the latest from the back row at Wagga. Might find this easier and he is race fit now. MURPHYS REWARD NZ (8) performed below market expectations at Wagga last start but had commenced his campaign with a Leeton second three back and won his lone attempt at this distance. Former Tasmanian SINISTER (10) should find this easier than his first outing for the Turnbull barn at Bathurst. Improver.",
